<TEXT>
dominic olejniczak the green bay 
packers president for 24 years who hired legendary coach vince 
lombardi died saturday of complications from a series of strokes 
he was 80 
olejniczak after 10 years as mayor of green bay became 
president of the national football league team in 1958 inheriting 
a team that finished 110 in 1957 and had not had a winning record 
in 10 years 
olejniczak headed the search committee that brought lombardi to 
green bay as coach and general manager and lombardi led the team 
to five championships including two super bowl titles 
olejniczak was named chairman of the board in 1981 and retired 
in 1982 
