<TEXT>
communist rebels said sunday they 
would declare a unilateral ceasefire and enter into peace talks if 
president corazon aquino promises to close us bases here by 1991 
the offer was contained in a statement by the rebel national 
democratic front which was delivered to news organizations 
in the statement the group said the united states was using its 
six military bases here to wage war and aggression in the 
pacific and to impose and maintain the prevailing system of 
oppression in this former american colony 
the united states maintains clark air base the subic bay naval 
base and four smaller installations under an agreement that expires 
in 1991 mrs aquino has refused to say whether she will support an 
extension which would require approval of twothirds of the 
23member senate 
the rebel statement said if the government ends the agreement on 
the bases the national democratic front would not hesitate to 
immediately declare a unilateral ceasefire and enter into 
negotiations for a comprehensive political settlement and a 
peaceful end to the civil war 
the front said that if mrs aquino refused it would call upon 
the revolutionary filipino people to themselves dismantle the 
bases 
the front is a confederation of 12 outlawed organizations 
including the communist party of the philippines and its military 
wing the new peoples army the rebels have been waging a 20year 
insurgency to establish a marxist state 
